1
00:00:01,268 --> 00:00:02,536
( Singing in Japanese )

2
00:00:02,569 --> 00:00:05,338
♪

3
00:00:18,252 --> 00:00:19,487
♪ Fire

4
00:00:19,520 --> 00:00:21,655
( singing in Japanese )

5
00:00:44,711 --> 00:00:46,813
( Insects chirping )

6
00:00:52,853 --> 00:00:53,854
( Norman sighs )

7
00:01:03,897 --> 00:01:05,198
( Clock ticking )

8
00:01:05,232 --> 00:01:06,867
Isabella: Are you
enjoying it here?

9
00:01:06,900 --> 00:01:09,703
Krone: Oh, of course.
Your children are a delight.

10
00:01:09,736 --> 00:01:12,272
They’re all so intelligent
and very well-behaved.

11
00:01:12,306 --> 00:01:15,209
Isabella: Quite.
And speaking of which,

12
00:01:15,242 --> 00:01:17,478
you’ve been
on your best behavior as well.

13
00:01:17,511 --> 00:01:18,846
Krone: Uh...

14
00:01:18,879 --> 00:01:20,481
- yes.
- ( Isabella chuckles )

15
00:01:20,514 --> 00:01:23,384
It’s good you’re trying
to gain their trust.

16
00:01:23,417 --> 00:01:25,419
you’ve even
played tag with them.

17
00:01:25,452 --> 00:01:28,255
i was worried
you’d be too spontaneous,

18
00:01:28,288 --> 00:01:29,523
but it’s been fine.

19
00:01:29,556 --> 00:01:30,724
( Krone sighs )

20
00:01:30,757 --> 00:01:32,592
Isabella: You’re just insurance.

21
00:01:32,626 --> 00:01:35,562
The only reason I called for you
in the first place

22
00:01:35,596 --> 00:01:38,332
was simply to make sure that
the products were protected.

23
00:01:38,365 --> 00:01:39,433
( Krone grunts )

24
00:01:39,466 --> 00:01:40,767
Isabella: So, you see,

25
00:01:40,801 --> 00:01:44,405
those who know the secret
are not your concern.

26
00:01:44,438 --> 00:01:47,374
All you have to do
is keep working hard,

27
00:01:47,407 --> 00:01:49,743
pretend to be obedient to me,

28
00:01:49,776 --> 00:01:51,745
and laugh about having leverage.

29
00:01:51,778 --> 00:01:53,446
( Krone gasps )
I-I would never...

30
00:01:53,480 --> 00:01:56,316
Isabella: Your sole purpose
for being at this house

31
00:01:56,350 --> 00:01:58,819
is to act as my pawn.

32
00:02:00,888 --> 00:02:03,324
But if you behave...

33
00:02:07,361 --> 00:02:10,698
I’ll award you the mom position
that you so desire.

34
00:02:10,731 --> 00:02:11,832
You have my word.

35
00:02:11,865 --> 00:02:13,533
( Krone gasps )

36
00:02:13,567 --> 00:02:16,437
♪

37
00:02:16,470 --> 00:02:19,173
Now, I know you’re a smart girl,

38
00:02:19,206 --> 00:02:22,443
so try not to make
any more errors.

39
00:02:22,476 --> 00:02:23,610
( Door closes )

40
00:02:23,644 --> 00:02:25,579
( Insects chirping )

41
00:02:35,489 --> 00:02:37,791
( Door closes )

42
00:02:37,824 --> 00:02:40,460
( Footsteps approaching )

43
00:02:40,494 --> 00:02:41,929
( Krone sighs )

44
00:02:44,665 --> 00:02:45,733
( Sighs )

45
00:02:48,502 --> 00:02:49,470
( Inhales )

46
00:02:49,503 --> 00:02:51,438
( Growling )

47
00:02:55,909 --> 00:02:58,812
How dare she?

48
00:02:59,913 --> 00:03:01,515
( Grunting )

49
00:03:02,583 --> 00:03:05,286
Just watch! You’ll see!

50
00:03:05,319 --> 00:03:08,255
I’ll drag you down, you witch!

51
00:03:08,288 --> 00:03:09,456
( Grunts )

52
00:03:09,489 --> 00:03:11,424
( Panting )

53
00:03:13,260 --> 00:03:15,662
( Chuckling )

54
00:03:17,431 --> 00:03:22,202
and then,
soon I will be mom here.

55
00:03:26,573 --> 00:03:27,741
- Norman: Emma!
- Emma: Huh?

56
00:03:27,774 --> 00:03:29,409
Norman: We should
start playing tag

57
00:03:29,443 --> 00:03:31,512
- in teams from now on.
- Emma: Why’s that?

58
00:03:31,545 --> 00:03:35,282
Ray: Honestly? Most would die
if they escaped on their own.

59
00:03:35,315 --> 00:03:36,750
Emma: Come on, ray!

60
00:03:36,783 --> 00:03:39,419
Ray: Not to say that they
don’t have some potential,

61
00:03:39,453 --> 00:03:41,422
but we shouldn’t
let them run solo.

62
00:03:41,455 --> 00:03:44,024
Norman: We’ll make formations
and take off in teams.

63
00:03:44,057 --> 00:03:47,060
ray: That way,
we can simulate the real escape.

64
00:03:47,094 --> 00:03:48,429
Emma: The real one?

65
00:03:48,462 --> 00:03:50,364
norman:
I had another idea as well.

66
00:03:50,397 --> 00:03:51,498
- Ray: Hmm?
- Emma: Oh?

67
00:03:51,532 --> 00:03:53,401
Norman: Let’s tell
Don and gilda.

68
00:03:53,433 --> 00:03:56,603
If we get them on our side,
they can be team leaders.

69
00:03:56,637 --> 00:03:59,507
Ray: And what if they turn out
to be mom’s informants?

70
00:03:59,540 --> 00:04:01,275
Norman: Don’t worry.

71
00:04:01,308 --> 00:04:04,344
I’ll basically be killing
two birds with one stone.

72
00:04:04,378 --> 00:04:05,846
Just leave it all to me.

73
00:04:05,879 --> 00:04:08,715
I’ve already made arrangements.

74
00:04:08,749 --> 00:04:09,883
Emma: Ah.

75
00:04:09,917 --> 00:04:11,352
- Ray: Emma.
- Emma: Mm?

76
00:04:11,385 --> 00:04:13,954
ray: Listen up.
Memorize these formations.

77
00:04:13,987 --> 00:04:15,455
There are 100 of them.

78
00:04:15,489 --> 00:04:17,458
Emma: Wait. Do you mean by ear?

79
00:04:17,491 --> 00:04:18,792
Ray: That a problem?

80
00:04:20,727 --> 00:04:21,795
Emma: Easy peasy.

81
00:04:24,097 --> 00:04:28,034
- ( Overlapping chatter )
- Child: ...So much fun.

82
00:04:28,068 --> 00:04:30,070
Ray: The goal here
is to not get caught.

83
00:04:30,103 --> 00:04:31,071
You have ten minutes.

84
00:04:31,104 --> 00:04:32,672
Go!

85
00:04:32,706 --> 00:04:34,007
♪

86
00:04:35,509 --> 00:04:37,344
Emma: Everyone, follow me!

87
00:04:37,377 --> 00:04:39,446
norman:
Let’s surprise ray by winning!

88
00:04:39,479 --> 00:04:41,047
( Children laughing )

89
00:04:41,081 --> 00:04:42,583
Don: We got this in the bag!

90
00:04:49,723 --> 00:04:51,658
♪

91
00:05:07,975 --> 00:05:09,310
( Emma chuckles )

92
00:05:09,343 --> 00:05:10,945
( Phil laughs )

93
00:05:20,554 --> 00:05:21,922
( Ray chuckles )

94
00:05:21,955 --> 00:05:24,124
( Overlapping chatter )

95
00:05:24,157 --> 00:05:26,526
Phil: That was so fun!

96
00:05:26,560 --> 00:05:28,662
Emma: You did pretty amazing
out there, Phil!

97
00:05:28,695 --> 00:05:30,697
Don: Hey, can we do that again?

98
00:05:30,731 --> 00:05:32,700
and, this time,
I want to be the leader.

99
00:05:32,733 --> 00:05:35,803
Gilda: Maybe we should
take a little break first.

100
00:05:35,836 --> 00:05:37,104
Child: Let’s do it again.

101
00:05:38,805 --> 00:05:41,608
Emma: This was a great idea!
I think it’ll work!

102
00:05:41,642 --> 00:05:42,977
Ray: Hmm.

103
00:05:44,444 --> 00:05:46,680
Emma, what’s phil’s score?

104
00:05:46,713 --> 00:05:48,548
Emma: Huh?

105
00:05:48,582 --> 00:05:50,551
His score, huh?

106
00:05:50,584 --> 00:05:53,821
i’m pretty sure
he’s averaging about 203.

107
00:05:53,854 --> 00:05:55,122
Norman: Pretty high.

108
00:05:55,155 --> 00:05:58,825
Ray: When we played tag
with sister and now,

109
00:05:58,859 --> 00:06:01,462
he was one of the last left.
How odd.

110
00:06:01,495 --> 00:06:02,596
Emma: Hmm?

111
00:06:02,629 --> 00:06:04,531
Ray: And, on top of that,

112
00:06:04,565 --> 00:06:07,101
he and Sherry are always
looking for you two.

113
00:06:07,134 --> 00:06:08,068
Emma: Uh...

114
00:06:09,703 --> 00:06:12,139
Hmm. ( Gasps )

115
00:06:12,172 --> 00:06:13,774
( Wails ) Stop it!

116
00:06:13,807 --> 00:06:15,942
I don’t wanna suspect him!
There’s no way!

117
00:06:15,976 --> 00:06:17,878
Ray: You’ve gotta start
being more suspicious

118
00:06:17,911 --> 00:06:19,146
of everyone, you dummy!

119
00:06:19,179 --> 00:06:21,515
This is life or death.

120
00:06:21,548 --> 00:06:24,451
( Emma whimpers )

121
00:06:24,484 --> 00:06:25,986
♪

122
00:06:29,223 --> 00:06:30,591
( Grunts )

123
00:06:30,624 --> 00:06:31,725
( Sighs )

124
00:06:32,860 --> 00:06:34,628
- Norman: Hey, ray.
- ray: Hmm?

125
00:06:34,661 --> 00:06:37,697
Norman: Are you any closer to
breaking the tracking devices?

126
00:06:37,731 --> 00:06:39,800
How much time do you need?

127
00:06:39,833 --> 00:06:41,435
Ray: Let’s see here.

128
00:06:41,468 --> 00:06:42,636
About ten days.

129
00:06:42,669 --> 00:06:44,804
norman: Right.
Then ten days from now.

130
00:06:44,838 --> 00:06:46,506
- Ray: Huh?
- ( Emma gasps )

131
00:06:46,540 --> 00:06:48,442
Norman: That’s when we’ll
break out of this place,

132
00:06:48,475 --> 00:06:49,443
on November 8th.

133
00:06:49,476 --> 00:06:51,044
( Both gasp )

134
00:06:51,078 --> 00:06:53,047
Emma: W-wait!

135
00:06:53,080 --> 00:06:54,148
That’s so soon!

136
00:06:54,181 --> 00:06:55,482
Which is fine, but--

137
00:06:55,516 --> 00:06:56,784
ray: Are you crazy?!

138
00:06:56,817 --> 00:06:58,886
Conny was shipped two weeks ago,

139
00:06:58,919 --> 00:07:01,021
and shipments go out
every two months,

140
00:07:01,054 --> 00:07:03,423
so we should have
a month and a half!

141
00:07:03,457 --> 00:07:05,125
weren’t we
supposed to use that time

142
00:07:05,158 --> 00:07:06,960
to carefully prepare our plan?!

143
00:07:06,994 --> 00:07:09,730
Norman: Yeah. But, see,
you’re only thinking that way

144
00:07:09,763 --> 00:07:13,133
because mom is controlling us
to think that way,

145
00:07:13,167 --> 00:07:15,002
so I say we outwit her.

146
00:07:15,035 --> 00:07:16,770
( Emma gasps )

147
00:07:16,803 --> 00:07:19,639
Ray: We’re likely to fail
if we rush. What then, Norman?

148
00:07:19,673 --> 00:07:22,543
Norman: We need to escape
before winter comes.

149
00:07:22,576 --> 00:07:26,847
Once we break the devices,
we’ll execute the escape plan.

150
00:07:26,880 --> 00:07:30,150
Emma: Then we’ve got a little
over a week to do everything.

151
00:07:30,184 --> 00:07:31,185
( Norman grunts )

152
00:07:31,218 --> 00:07:33,187
( Ray scoffs )

153
00:07:33,220 --> 00:07:36,857
Emma: So let’s talk to Don and
gilda about the plan tonight.

154
00:07:37,925 --> 00:07:39,794
( Insects chirping )

155
00:07:39,826 --> 00:07:41,795
( Footsteps clomping )

156
00:07:41,829 --> 00:07:43,764
♪

157
00:08:01,615 --> 00:08:03,550
( Stairs creaking )

158
00:08:30,844 --> 00:08:33,080
Emma: Please, guys,
just follow my lead.

159
00:08:33,113 --> 00:08:34,247
Ray: Huh?

160
00:08:34,281 --> 00:08:35,282
( Norman grunts )

161
00:08:35,315 --> 00:08:37,150
( Don and gilda gasp )

162
00:08:38,252 --> 00:08:39,754
Don: Hey, Emma! What’s up?

163
00:08:39,786 --> 00:08:40,987
( Gilda sighs )

164
00:08:43,657 --> 00:08:46,627
Don: Human trafficking?
are you sure?

165
00:08:46,660 --> 00:08:49,596
( Gilda gasps )

166
00:08:51,064 --> 00:08:53,900
emma: Yeah.
All of our siblings...

167
00:08:53,934 --> 00:08:56,103
were sold off
to some really bad people.

168
00:08:56,136 --> 00:08:58,305
( Don gasps ) Uh...

169
00:08:58,338 --> 00:09:02,108
( Laughs )

170
00:09:02,142 --> 00:09:05,045
No, no, no! There’s no way!
Come on!

171
00:09:05,078 --> 00:09:06,913
Norman: It explains
the walls and gate

172
00:09:06,947 --> 00:09:09,016
and also why the kids
who get adopted

173
00:09:09,049 --> 00:09:10,884
never send us any letters.

174
00:09:10,918 --> 00:09:12,653
Don: All right, guys.

175
00:09:12,686 --> 00:09:13,854
So what’s the punch line?

176
00:09:13,887 --> 00:09:15,889
You almost had me there
for a second.

177
00:09:15,923 --> 00:09:17,691
( Emma stammers )

178
00:09:19,092 --> 00:09:21,761
Don: Uh, hey...

179
00:09:21,795 --> 00:09:23,897
Why aren’t you guys
saying anything?

180
00:09:23,931 --> 00:09:25,599
Ray: Because it’s true.

181
00:09:25,632 --> 00:09:27,200
Don: What?

182
00:09:27,234 --> 00:09:29,870
Wait, but mom...

183
00:09:29,903 --> 00:09:31,605
Emma: She’s the one...

184
00:09:32,739 --> 00:09:34,274
Who sells us to people.

185
00:09:34,308 --> 00:09:37,878
Don: Huh?! There’s no way
mom would ever do that to us!

186
00:09:37,911 --> 00:09:39,813
Take it back, Emma!

187
00:09:39,847 --> 00:09:42,283
- Gilda: Don.
- Don: Huh?

188
00:09:42,316 --> 00:09:44,852
Gilda: Emma loves mom
and this house

189
00:09:44,885 --> 00:09:47,621
just as much as the rest of us.

190
00:09:47,654 --> 00:09:49,789
Why would she make this up?

191
00:09:49,823 --> 00:09:51,925
( Don gasps )

192
00:09:51,959 --> 00:09:53,327
Emma: So, gilda...

193
00:09:53,360 --> 00:09:57,331
Gilda: To tell the truth,
I did think it was weird.

194
00:09:57,364 --> 00:10:00,367
The night that conny left,

195
00:10:00,400 --> 00:10:03,236
emma and Norman
both went down to the gate.

196
00:10:03,270 --> 00:10:05,105
Don: Wait. You did?

197
00:10:05,138 --> 00:10:06,673
Norman: Yeah.

198
00:10:06,707 --> 00:10:09,410
Gilda: In most cases,
even if you broke the rules,

199
00:10:09,443 --> 00:10:11,111
you’d eventually
come clean about it,

200
00:10:11,144 --> 00:10:13,079
and things
would go back to normal.

201
00:10:13,113 --> 00:10:14,848
But you haven’t done that yet.

202
00:10:14,882 --> 00:10:16,684
( Emma gasps )

203
00:10:16,717 --> 00:10:17,885
( Don gasps )

204
00:10:17,918 --> 00:10:20,821
gilda: Emma,
I wanted to ask about it,

205
00:10:20,854 --> 00:10:23,924
but I always got too scared
to bring it up.

206
00:10:25,125 --> 00:10:27,060
( Crying )

207
00:10:30,030 --> 00:10:32,399
Emma: Oh, gilda,
oh, please don’t cry.

208
00:10:32,432 --> 00:10:34,901
I’m sorry I made you worry.

209
00:10:34,935 --> 00:10:37,204
Gilda: Did you see it happen?

210
00:10:37,237 --> 00:10:41,775
Did you guys see conny being
sold off to the bad people?

211
00:10:43,210 --> 00:10:44,712
- ( Emma grunts )
- Norman: Yeah...

212
00:10:44,745 --> 00:10:47,081
But we didn’t make it in time.

213
00:10:47,114 --> 00:10:49,249
Don: Okay, but is conny safe?

214
00:10:49,283 --> 00:10:50,251
Norman: I don’t know.

215
00:10:50,284 --> 00:10:51,218
( Ray sighs )

216
00:10:53,387 --> 00:10:55,256
Don: Impossible.

217
00:10:55,289 --> 00:10:57,158
This can’t be real!

218
00:10:58,792 --> 00:11:00,527
Norman: I don’t know
if this proves much,

219
00:11:00,561 --> 00:11:02,797
but Emma and ray
spent the last few days

220
00:11:02,830 --> 00:11:05,733
looking into
everyone’s test scores.

221
00:11:05,766 --> 00:11:07,434
Both: Our test scores?

222
00:11:09,236 --> 00:11:11,805
Norman: According to this,
kids over six

223
00:11:11,839 --> 00:11:14,842
are adopted in order
of lowest scores first.

224
00:11:14,875 --> 00:11:16,343
Weird, huh?

225
00:11:16,376 --> 00:11:20,947
Don: So not just conny’s scores,
but hao and ceddy.

226
00:11:20,981 --> 00:11:23,317
Gilda: It’s just
like Norman said.

227
00:11:23,350 --> 00:11:25,252
Emma: Don, gilda...

228
00:11:25,285 --> 00:11:28,955
let’s all escape
so that we can help everyone.

229
00:11:28,989 --> 00:11:31,458
we can do it
if we work together!

230
00:11:31,491 --> 00:11:33,393
Please, help us.

231
00:11:33,427 --> 00:11:34,395
( Don sighs )

232
00:11:38,232 --> 00:11:39,266
( Both grunt )

233
00:11:40,501 --> 00:11:43,070
( Emma chuckles )

234
00:11:43,103 --> 00:11:44,471
( Gasps )

235
00:11:44,505 --> 00:11:46,073
( Ray sighs )

236
00:11:46,106 --> 00:11:47,407
♪

237
00:11:51,979 --> 00:11:53,180
Ray: What was that?

238
00:11:53,213 --> 00:11:54,881
Norman: Not to your liking?

239
00:11:54,915 --> 00:11:56,784
Ray: "So we can help everyone"?

240
00:11:56,817 --> 00:11:58,919
You should have told them
they died!

241
00:11:58,952 --> 00:12:01,922
Norman: We did what we had to
so they’d join us.

242
00:12:01,955 --> 00:12:04,024
Ray: If they end up
not being spies,

243
00:12:04,057 --> 00:12:06,860
then that was a cruel thing
to do to someone.

244
00:12:06,894 --> 00:12:10,164
Conny is dead. You shouldn’t
have given them false hope!

245
00:12:11,865 --> 00:12:15,302
they need the truth.
When are you going to tell them?

246
00:12:15,335 --> 00:12:16,436
Can you?

247
00:12:16,470 --> 00:12:18,806
Norman: Maybe when
the time is right.

248
00:12:18,839 --> 00:12:21,308
We still have to assume
they might be spies,

249
00:12:21,341 --> 00:12:23,376
so then we should lay a trap.

250
00:12:23,410 --> 00:12:25,412
Ray: A trap?

251
00:12:25,445 --> 00:12:27,847
Norman: I’m going to tell them
where the rope is hidden.

252
00:12:27,881 --> 00:12:29,850
( Ray groans )

253
00:12:29,883 --> 00:12:32,285
Norman: I’ll tell Don
that it’s behind my bed.

254
00:12:32,319 --> 00:12:33,554
Gilda will know that it’s

255
00:12:33,587 --> 00:12:36,356
in the second-floor
bathroom’s ceiling,

256
00:12:36,390 --> 00:12:39,827
and at that point
how’s mom gonna find out?

257
00:12:39,860 --> 00:12:41,362
We’ll just have to see.

258
00:12:41,395 --> 00:12:44,498
Ray: Okay, but what if
the ropes are gone

259
00:12:44,531 --> 00:12:46,900
and it turns out that
neither of them are the spy?

260
00:12:46,934 --> 00:12:50,037
Norman: I’ve already
considered that.

261
00:12:50,070 --> 00:12:52,306
Ray: Seems like you’re
prepared for everything.

262
00:12:52,339 --> 00:12:53,907
- Norman: Yeah, I told you.
- ( Ray gasps )

263
00:12:53,941 --> 00:12:55,543
Norman: The key here
is to outwit.

264
00:12:55,576 --> 00:12:57,545
( Ray grunts )

265
00:12:57,578 --> 00:12:59,346
( Children chattering )

266
00:12:59,379 --> 00:13:01,781
Emma: You remember?
It was so fun!

267
00:13:01,815 --> 00:13:02,949
( Gilda giggles )

268
00:13:02,983 --> 00:13:04,284
This is nice, Emma.

269
00:13:04,318 --> 00:13:06,821
it’s been a while
since we talked like this.

270
00:13:06,854 --> 00:13:10,157
emma: Weird, right?
Since we’re always together.

271
00:13:12,860 --> 00:13:17,031
Gilda: Let’s keep it that way,
together forever.

272
00:13:17,064 --> 00:13:18,999
( Emma gasps )

273
00:13:19,032 --> 00:13:19,966
( Giggles )

274
00:13:21,101 --> 00:13:22,035
Yeah.

275
00:13:25,038 --> 00:13:26,773
( Clock ticking )

276
00:14:01,708 --> 00:14:03,443
( Emma gasps )

277
00:14:05,012 --> 00:14:06,947
( Footsteps shuffling )

278
00:14:13,587 --> 00:14:14,755
( Isabella gasps )

279
00:14:15,923 --> 00:14:16,957
( Sighs )

280
00:14:16,990 --> 00:14:19,493
♪

281
00:14:29,603 --> 00:14:30,771
I see.

282
00:14:30,804 --> 00:14:33,907
the rope is
in norman’s bed, is it?

283
00:14:39,880 --> 00:14:41,248
( Krone chuckles )

284
00:14:41,281 --> 00:14:43,216
I’ve been waiting
for you, gilda.

285
00:14:43,250 --> 00:14:44,251
( Emma gasps )

286
00:14:44,284 --> 00:14:46,219
♪

287
00:15:03,871 --> 00:15:06,507
Krone: We can talk now,
can’t we?

288
00:15:06,540 --> 00:15:07,541
( Emma gasps )

289
00:15:07,574 --> 00:15:10,110
Gilda: You mean about...

290
00:15:10,143 --> 00:15:11,177
The issue, right?

291
00:15:20,120 --> 00:15:22,055
( Stammering )

292
00:15:23,757 --> 00:15:25,759
Well, there isn’t an issue!

293
00:15:25,792 --> 00:15:28,061
i appreciate you
checking in on me so much,

294
00:15:28,095 --> 00:15:30,230
but there’s nothing
to worry about.

295
00:15:30,264 --> 00:15:33,567
krone: Are you sure?
I can’t help but be concerned.

296
00:15:33,600 --> 00:15:35,569
Gilda: I feel better, I promise,

297
00:15:35,602 --> 00:15:37,938
so please stop
worrying about me.

298
00:15:37,971 --> 00:15:39,506
- Good night.
- ( Emma gasping )

299
00:15:42,576 --> 00:15:44,611
Krone: Ah, I see now.

300
00:15:44,645 --> 00:15:46,747
Emma told you everything.

301
00:15:46,780 --> 00:15:49,182
Hmm? ( Laughs )

302
00:15:50,284 --> 00:15:52,286
Am I right, gilda?

303
00:15:52,319 --> 00:15:55,722
she told you
all about it, didn’t she?

304
00:15:55,756 --> 00:15:58,726
( Gilda gasping )

305
00:15:58,759 --> 00:16:00,327
( Krone chuckles )

306
00:16:00,360 --> 00:16:02,262
( Emma gasps )

307
00:16:02,296 --> 00:16:04,265
Krone: Ahh!

308
00:16:04,298 --> 00:16:06,600
Too bad. I was really hoping

309
00:16:06,633 --> 00:16:08,568
that we could eventually
become good friends.

310
00:16:08,602 --> 00:16:10,704
( Chuckles ) So tell me.

311
00:16:10,737 --> 00:16:12,706
How many of the others know?

312
00:16:12,739 --> 00:16:14,774
There’s Norman and ray.

313
00:16:14,808 --> 00:16:16,109
Anyone else?

314
00:16:16,143 --> 00:16:19,213
( Gilda gasps )

315
00:16:19,246 --> 00:16:22,116
krone: I will let you
off the hook if you cooperate,

316
00:16:22,149 --> 00:16:23,250
so let’s work together.

317
00:16:23,283 --> 00:16:27,187
♪

318
00:16:32,826 --> 00:16:34,861
Gilda: Please stop this!

319
00:16:34,895 --> 00:16:37,197
( Sighing )

320
00:16:37,231 --> 00:16:39,767
What are you
even talking about?

321
00:16:39,800 --> 00:16:41,802
Emma and I just had a fight,

322
00:16:41,835 --> 00:16:44,905
but we were able to make up,
so everything’s fine now!

323
00:16:46,173 --> 00:16:47,608
( Krone laughs )

324
00:16:47,641 --> 00:16:50,210
well, it appears
that I misunderstood. Sorry.

325
00:16:50,244 --> 00:16:52,246
( Gilda gasps )

326
00:16:54,214 --> 00:16:56,783
Krone: If you think
Emma is lying to you,

327
00:16:56,817 --> 00:16:59,019
feel free to come back
and talk to me.

328
00:16:59,052 --> 00:17:00,720
( Gilda gasps )

329
00:17:02,055 --> 00:17:03,690
Krone: Sweet dreams, gilda.

330
00:17:03,724 --> 00:17:05,192
( Door creaks )

331
00:17:07,227 --> 00:17:09,162
( Clock ticking )

332
00:17:13,867 --> 00:17:15,869
( Gilda gasps ) Emma.

333
00:17:15,903 --> 00:17:16,904
Emma: Gilda.

334
00:17:16,937 --> 00:17:18,872
( Gilda whimpering )

335
00:17:26,813 --> 00:17:27,781
( Krone groans )

336
00:17:27,814 --> 00:17:29,983
I am not giving up.

337
00:17:30,017 --> 00:17:32,887
If I can’t get gilda, then...

338
00:17:35,789 --> 00:17:37,824
thank you
for all your help, Don.

339
00:17:37,858 --> 00:17:39,293
Don: Yeah, no problem!

340
00:17:39,326 --> 00:17:41,762
Gilda: You think
we should be worried?

341
00:17:41,795 --> 00:17:44,998
Emma: It’s time to go.
Mom’s watching.

342
00:17:45,032 --> 00:17:47,034
( Overlapping chatter )

343
00:17:49,736 --> 00:17:54,274
Norman: According to what Emma
told me, we can trust gilda.

344
00:17:54,308 --> 00:17:58,312
I’m curious. Why do you think
the traitor’s betraying us?

345
00:17:58,345 --> 00:18:01,815
Ray: It’s obvious that there’s
gotta be some sort of advantage.

346
00:18:01,849 --> 00:18:03,250
Think about it.

347
00:18:03,283 --> 00:18:06,086
maybe they get spared
from being shipped or something.

348
00:18:06,119 --> 00:18:07,954
( Norman gasps )

349
00:18:07,988 --> 00:18:11,291
Guaranteed survival. Huh.

350
00:18:11,325 --> 00:18:13,260
( Children panting )

351
00:18:16,129 --> 00:18:17,764
Don: Oh, I get it now.

352
00:18:17,798 --> 00:18:19,633
This was all escape training,
wasn’t it?

353
00:18:25,305 --> 00:18:28,341
Emma: 1, 2, 3...

354
00:18:28,375 --> 00:18:29,710
Norman: Emma.

355
00:18:29,743 --> 00:18:30,711
Emma: Eh?

356
00:18:30,744 --> 00:18:32,246
Norman: Can we talk?

357
00:18:32,279 --> 00:18:35,048
I need your thoughts
on something.

358
00:18:35,082 --> 00:18:36,216
Emma: Hmm?

359
00:18:36,250 --> 00:18:38,252
Norman: If there
really is someone here

360
00:18:38,285 --> 00:18:40,487
who’s willingly siding
with the demons

361
00:18:40,521 --> 00:18:42,289
and is guaranteed to live

362
00:18:42,322 --> 00:18:44,858
in exchange
for bits of information--

363
00:18:44,892 --> 00:18:47,294
Emma: You mean that they’re safe
from getting shipped out

364
00:18:47,327 --> 00:18:50,096
- because they’re spying on us?
- Norman: Mm-hmm.

365
00:18:50,130 --> 00:18:52,799
Would you take them with us
or just leave them?

366
00:18:52,833 --> 00:18:55,002
Emma: Hmm.

367
00:18:55,035 --> 00:18:56,003
I’d take them.

368
00:18:56,036 --> 00:18:57,404
( Norman gasps )

369
00:18:57,437 --> 00:19:00,140
Even if they didn’t want that?

370
00:19:00,174 --> 00:19:01,942
Emma: Mm-hmm. I’d force them.

371
00:19:01,975 --> 00:19:04,077
Because if we end up escaping,

372
00:19:04,111 --> 00:19:07,081
then that person’s life
might not be guaranteed anymore.

373
00:19:07,114 --> 00:19:08,882
( Norman gasps )

374
00:19:08,916 --> 00:19:12,787
emma: And plus
I wanna believe in everyone.

375
00:19:12,819 --> 00:19:15,322
i realized that
after what happened with gilda.

376
00:19:15,355 --> 00:19:18,291
Ray said to suspect everyone,

377
00:19:18,325 --> 00:19:21,161
but even if one of us
is helping the demons,

378
00:19:21,195 --> 00:19:23,698
none of our siblings
are truly bad.

379
00:19:24,765 --> 00:19:26,734
We all grew up together!

380
00:19:26,767 --> 00:19:30,237
Even if someone gets in our way
or says i’m naive,

381
00:19:30,270 --> 00:19:32,072
I still wanna believe in them.

382
00:19:34,441 --> 00:19:35,909
Right.

383
00:19:35,943 --> 00:19:38,446
of course
that would be your answer.

384
00:19:38,478 --> 00:19:40,981
♪

385
00:19:42,049 --> 00:19:42,983
( Footstep thumps )

386
00:20:02,236 --> 00:20:03,204
( Ray grunts )

387
00:20:03,237 --> 00:20:04,905
( Norman grunts )

388
00:20:07,107 --> 00:20:08,408
Ray: No rope?

389
00:20:10,477 --> 00:20:11,478
Norman: It’s gone.

390
00:20:11,512 --> 00:20:13,414
Ray: Really?

391
00:20:15,115 --> 00:20:17,484
Well, then, guess it was Don.

392
00:20:17,518 --> 00:20:19,053
( Norman grunts )

393
00:20:23,156 --> 00:20:26,459
Actually, it’s you
who’s the traitor, ray.

394
00:20:26,493 --> 00:20:29,196
( Ray gasps )

395
00:20:34,301 --> 00:20:35,269
♪

396
00:20:35,302 --> 00:20:37,237
( Singing in Japanese )

